messages.author: Vitaly Buka
messages.text:
Does this mean that callback will never be called.
Probably more convenient to guaranty that for every Start callback will be trigered

messages.author: Noam Samuel
messages.text:
On 2013/06/21 19:35:25, Vitaly Buka wrote:
> Does this mean that callback will never be called.
> Probably more convenient to guaranty that for every Start callback will be
> trigered

No, this means the callback will only be called once per Start() call. Since UNSPECIFIED has two transactions, we only call the callback if both have failed.
